{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 11:31:43.255831", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nExecutive summary\n- Overall network health: Good. End-to-end IP and DNS connectivity works as designed. OSPF adjacencies are Full across core, distribution, and server-access routers. The HTTP services (web0–web3, web99 via Nginx) are reachable from user hosts. Back-end servers are correctly isolated (not reachable from hosts).\n- Notable observation: HTTP total times are consistently ~1.0–1.1s from hosts and from the load balancer, while TTFB is ~0.20–0.34s. This looks like an application-layer behavior rather than a network fault.\n\nKey findings and evidence\n\n1) Host addressing and basic reachability\n- Host IPs: host_1_1_1_1 = 10.1.1.10, host_2_1_1_1 = 10.2.1.10 (consistent with 10.<core>.<dist>.0/24 scheme).\n- Host-to-DNS reachability: OK\n  - host_1_1_1_1 -> 10.200.0.2: 0% loss, ~2.15 ms avg\n  - host_2_1_1_1 -> 10.200.0.2: 0% loss, ~2.86 ms avg\n- Host-to-server farm reachability: OK\n  - host_1_1_1_1 -> 10.200.0.3/4/5/6: 0% loss, ~2–4 ms avg\n  - host_1_1_1_1 -> load_balancer 10.200.0.7: 0% loss, ~2.4 ms avg\n  - host_1_1_1_1 -> dhcp_server 10.200.0.8: 0% loss, ~3.55 ms avg\n\n2) DNS and HTTP service validation\n- DNS resolution for web99.local and web[0–3].local works with fast name lookup (~3–18 ms on first lookup; ~3–5 ms subsequent).\n- HTTP health from hosts:\n  - http://web99.local: total ~1.00–1.12 s, TTFB ~0.20–0.32 s (both hosts similar)\n  - http://web0.local … http://web3.local: total ~0.98–1.13 s, TTFB ~0.22–0.34 s\n- Web servers listening:\n  - web_server_[0–3]: python3 listening on 0.0.0.0:80\n  - load_balancer: nginx listening on 0.0.0.0:80\n- Load balancer configuration (nginx):\n  - upstream web99 includes backends 20.200.0.2:80, 20.200.0.3:80, 20.200.0.4:80\n  - LB -> backends:\n    - ICMP: 0% loss, <1 ms RTT\n    - HTTP (curl to 20.200.0.2): TTFB ~0.27–0.30 s, total ~1.07–1.10 s\n\n3) Backend isolation (policy check)\n- From hosts (10.1.1.0/24, 10.2.1.0/24) to backend subnet 20.200.0.0/24:\n  - ICMP to 20.200.0.2/3/4 fails as expected; explicit \"Destination Net Unreachable\" returned by gateway (10.1.1.1). \n  - curl to 20.200.0.2/3/4 times out from host.\n- Routing tables confirm no route leakage to 20.200.0.0/24:\n  - server_access_router advertises 10.200.0.0/24 via br0; no 20.200.0.0/24 in OSPF.\n  - core routers have OSPF routes to 10.200.0.0/24 but no routes to 20.200.0.0/24.\n- LB and backends are in 20.200.0.0/24 locally:\n  - LB eth1 = 20.200.0.1/24; backend_web_0 eth0 = 20.200.0.2/24; direct connectivity OK.\n\n4) OSPF control-plane status\n- Neighbors: All core routers, both distribution routers, and server_access_router show Full adjacencies on appropriate interlinks. Neighbor up-times ~1m40s during checks; dead timers decrementing normally.\n- Routes:\n  - 10.200.0.0/24: present via server_access_router on all cores.\n  - 10.1.1.0/24 and 10.2.1.0/24 present across core and server_access segments with correct next-hops.\n  - No OSPF presence for 20.200.0.0/24 (consistent with isolation requirements).\n\nDetected anomalies\n- None functionally significant. Connectivity, routing, DNS, and service exposure/isolation all match the intended design.\n\nNotable performance observation (not a fault localization)\n- Consistent HTTP total time ~1.0–1.1 s across direct web servers and via the load balancer, with TTFB ~0.20–0.34 s. The added ~0.7–0.9 s after TTFB suggests application-side behavior (e.g., content generation delay, connection handling, or timing in the test harness) rather than network latency (ICMP RTTs are ~1–4 ms). No packet loss observed at L3.\n\nConclusions\n- No current anomalies detected.\n- Fault localization: N/A (no faults).\n- Root cause: N/A (no faults). The only observation of slightly high HTTP total times appears to be application-layer behavior rather than a network problem.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 14039, "output_tokens": 4672, "total_tokens": 18711, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 11008}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 3392}}}
